I use this app 2 to 3 times a week since more than two years.  Overall, I think it's great, and definitely worth the money.  Nevertheless, there are some drawbacks: (1) In a given programme, all exercises are the same length: jogging in place for a minute is effortless, but pushups for a minute without stopping is for Arnold. (2) The timing 10/20/30 minutes for the "full" workout is too coarse.  I found 2 times 10 minutes ok, but a single 20 min programme quite tough. (3) A bug that's been there for years: The calculation of the calories consumed is erroneous: 10 minutes "full"  gets me 77 Cal, but if I add another 5 min stretching the total amount of calories spent gets less! (4) The stretching part is too static. (5) It would be nice to have programs like "light workout", "hard workout" etc.  So much for the critique.  Still, I like the app.
